<h3><b>Research experiences and achievements</b></h3>
<p>What I focused on the past few years was the applications of density-functional theory (DFT) calculations to understand how local surface and interface geometries control their functionalities by exploiting theoretical surface characterization approachesŌĆōwhich covers an electronic structure analysis, statistic thermodynamics, theoretical spectroscopy, and microscopy simulations. Below are the detailed topics I investigated until now;</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Oxidation of (bi)metal surfaces under controlled growth conditions</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Water-splitting reactions on oxide surfaces</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Development and application of theoretical surface characterizations of above surface processes</strong></li>
</ul>

